ang County. He also made use of many of the previously published Chinese-language descriptions of Xong. The results are of use to scholars with an interest in the Miao-Yao family in particular or in the languages of East and Southeast Asia more in general.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mrz 2022) 0aHmong languagexDialectsxGrammar. 0aHmong languagexGrammar. 4aGrammatik. 4aHmong-Mien. 4aMiao-Yao. 4aXong. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh  aGrammar.  aHmong-Mien.  aMiao-Yao.  aXong.0 cprintz978311058736440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311076493240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110764932423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110764932/original  aEBA_CL_LS  aEBA_DGALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK